News

May 8, 2017 - New York, NY - Special Materials Company (SMC) Appoints Michael Chernishenko to Develop New Specialty Phosphorus Derivatives Business

Special Materials Company (SMC) is pleased to announce the appointment of 
	Michael Chernishenko to the role of Phosphorus Products Business Development 
	Manager reporting directly to SMC Chief Executive, Adam Feldman. In this role 
	Chernishenko will be responsible for identifying and leading strategic business 
	development and commercial opportunities in the specialty phosphorus derivatives 
	area. 
Prior to joining SMC, Chernishenko was VP Business Development Industrial at 
	Digital Specialty Chemicals Ltd., a private corporation, specializing in the 
	development and manufacture of fine chemicals used in industrial processes, 
	biotech and pharmaceutical applications. Much of Chernishenko early career was 
	spent at Cytec Solvay Group where he held roles in R&D, Product Development, and 
	Product Management. 
"We are delighted Michael is joining us, he has both the technical and 
	commercial background having worked in the lab, plants, and the field. Most 
	importantly, he also shares our vision for the future and has a clear vision on 
	taking our specialty phosphorus derivatives business to the next level of 
	success," said Adam Feldman, Special Materials Company CEO. Chernishenko holds a 
	MBA from Niagara University, and a MSc. in Organic Chemistry and Biotechnology 
	from Brock University. He presently resides in Canada.

February 16, 2017 - New York, NY - Special Materials Company Growth is Reason for Expansion

Special Materials Company's continued growth in sales has fueled the need to 
	open a new chemical distribution center in Pageland, SC. The new 80,000 square 
	feet distribution hub will free up space in the production and tolling services 
	plant, Special Materials Company Industrial Services, located 20 miles south in 
	Kershaw, SC and provide getting products to market in a secure, reliable and 
	speedy fashion. 
"The Pageland distribution center is an important investment for us. This is 
	for our customers, to serve them better," said Kevin Huber, Founder and 
	Executive Vice President for Special Materials Company. "It is a direct result 
	of our continued commitment to provide a competitive advantage to customers and 
	deploy our supply chain activities from our strategic south east location." 
According to Jeff Walling, Director of Operations at Special Materials 
	Company, the new Pageland distribution center will provide additional storage 
	capacity and offer value-added services such as transportation, cross-docking, 
	order-fulfillment, labeling and packaging along with other services necessary to 
	complete the order cycle. "We're continuing to invest in the south east and 
	looking forward to this expansion in our continued growth," Jeff said.

April 30, 2016 - New York, NY - Special Materials Company (SMC) Receives "Gold Seal" Letter from U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)
Special Materials Company (SMC) has received EPA registrations for its Avancid® GL end use (click for letter) and manufacturing (click for letter) use glutaraldehyde containing biocides.  Inclusive of these EPA registrations, SMC has also received Gold Seal Letters of Certification from the EPA (also referred to as a "Pesticide Product Certificate of Registration") which certifies that SMC's glutaraldehyde products are legally registered in the U.S. with the Agency.  The "gold seal" letters affirm that SMC's Avancid® GL biocides are registered products under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act (FIFRA), and that these products may be sold and marketed in the United States as authorized and limited by FIFRA.
Registration of SMC's Avancid® GL glutaraldehyde biocides with the EPA denotes that SMC is responsible for ensuring full compliance with all laws regarding the sale, distribution, storage and/or disposal of these product.  According to SMC's Chief Operating Officer Michel DelliCompagni "Responsibility matters to Special Materials Company.  These registrations along with the Gold Seal Letters of Certification demonstrates SMC's commitment to maintain excellence by adhering to applicable laws, rules, and regulations with respect to our registered biocides."
SMC recently underwent an intensive registration process with the EPA and made a significant investment in registering these biocides at the federal and individual state levels.
The Avancid® GL series of glutaraldehyde based biocides have found wide-spread use in a variety of applications, particularly in oil and gas, industrial water treatment, process water systems,  and industrial preservation applications.  These products are now commercially available through SMC and the recently formed SMC Oilfield Chemicals Division.
For additional information on these products, please contact Charlie Neale @225-953-3823 or Lauren Bogie @ 918-202-3022.

December 23, 2015 - New York, NY - Lauren Bogie Appointed as Special Materials Company (SMC) Account Executive.
Special Materials Company is pleased to announce that Lauren Bogie from 
Tulsa, Oklahoma has joined SMC as an Account Executive for their North American 
region. 
Lauren brings over 10 years of experience in the chemical industry. She spent 
nine years with Brenntag Southwest in a variety of sales and management 
positions. Most recently, Lauren worked as an Account Executive for Chemjet, 
Inc. where she was responsible for sales and business development for specialty 
drilling fluid chemicals, additives, and specialty formulated lubricants for all 
types of drilling fluid systems. Lauren has a BA in Psychology with a minor in 
Chemistry from Northeastern State University. 
"Lauren will play a vital role in our evolution. Lauren will be involved in 
our Oilfield Chemicals Division as well as new business development within 
Oilfield, Water, and distribution," said Michael DelliCompagni, Special 
Materials Company Chief Operating Officer.

October 28, 2015 - New York, NY - Jim Love appointed new Vice-President of Business Development.
Special Materials Company (SMC) is pleased to announce the appointment of Jim 
Love as its new Vice-President of Business Development with immediate effect.

In his new position, Jim Love will be responsible for enable and develop a 
new specialty solvents business platform (CASE), assisting in various strategic 
growth programs, and will report into Adam Feldman, Special Materials Company's 
CEO. 
Commenting on the new appointment, Adam Feldman said: "Jim will be a great 
asset to the management team. In addition, the specialty solvents business is a 
perfect fit for SMC since these products are sold into the coatings, adhesives, 
sealants and elastomers (CASE) industries, along with pharmaceutical, industrial 
and natural gas processing industries. 
Jim has an extensive background in the Chemical Industry. Prior to joining 
SMC , he has held various executive and management roles including Vice 
President at Novolyte Performance Materials, (where he was in charge of their 
solvents business), Business Director of Performance Materials at Ferro 
Corporation, and Asia Expansion Manager at Ferro Corporation. Jim also has 
extensive experience in engineering and operations working for Stauffer 
Chemical, Rhodia, and as site manager at Ferro's Zachary, Louisiana plant. Most 
recently, Jim has been serving as President of Chem Development Group, a 
consulting company he founded to help companies in the specialty chemicals 
market space with various business development, marketing and technology 
commercialization initiatives. 
Jim has a BS in Chemical Engineering from Texas Tech, is a graduate of the 
LSU Executive Program, and has done post-graduate studies in business at Case 
Western Reserve University. 

June 23, 2015 - New York, NY - Special Materials Company wins 2015 Annual LCEDC Industry Golf Appreciation Tournament
On Tuesday, June 23rd, Special Materials Company won first 
place in the
2015 Lancaster County Economic Development Corporation (LCEDC) annual 
Industry Appreciation golf tournament hosted at the
Edgewater Golf Club in Lancaster, SC. 
SMC's team included the foursome of Shane Brewer, Heath 
Brewer, Jerry Pardue and Champ Williams who teamed for a 59. 
The golf tournament provided an opportunity for the LCEDC 
and local government to thank and recognize the many industries that call 
Lancaster County home.
Special Materials Company participation to the LCEDC 
tournament goes in line with its purpose of supporting actively the communities 
in which it operates.

May 26, 2015 - New York, NY - Leo Walsh Has Been Appointed Business Manager for the Paint & Coatings Market
Special Materials Company (SMC) has appointed Leo Walsh as new Compliance 
Solutions Business Manager. Mr. Walsh will be tasked with deepening SMC's 
already established leading North America supplier position of the low VOC 
solvent parachlorobenzotrifluoride, as well 
as implementing commercial strategies for other key solvent products: 
monochlorotolune, dimethyl carbonate 
and propylene carbonate. 
According to Kevin Huber, Special Materials Company Co-founder and Executive 
Vice President "Leo brings over 30 years of sales and strategic raw material 
sourcing experience all built as a chemist and coupled with exceptional 
technical aptitude. There is no doubt he will enlarge SMC's industry reputation 
primarily in the paint and coatings markets." 
Prior to joining Special Materials Company (SMC), Leo Walsh was an account 
manager with Sensient Technology Corporation and manager of strategic materials 
with Henkel/Cognis Corporation. He has also held other process and research 
chemist positions with Henkel and National Starch & Chemical Company. 
Leo Walsh summarized why he joined Special Materials Company (SMC) by 
stating, "I consider myself an out of the box thinker and appreciate the 
opportunity to be part of an organization that encourages independent thinking, 
responsible action, and entrepreneurial spirit."

October 30, 2014 - New York, NY - Special Materials Company (SMC) Announces a New Joint Venture with Dalian Bio Chem to Supply Isothiazolone Biocides and Preservatives to the U.S. Market
Special Materials Company (SMC) and Dalian Bio Chem have agreed to form a new 
joint venture in the isothiazolone-based biocide and preservative markets.
DBSM Biocides, will 
formulate, market and sell isothiazolone based biocides and preservatives 
throughout the U.S., offering customers a new alternative to their current 
isothiazolone supplier. 
The company is headquartered in New York City and has received full 
registration with the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) for its Extracide® CMIT/MIT series of biocides and preservatives. Investments are under way to 
fully support this business including manufacturing, warehousing and laboratory 
expansions to service DBSM Biocides' customers. 
"Dalian Bio-Chem is an excellent partner for Special Materials Company. They 
are clearly a leading manufacturer of technologically advanced and high quality 
biocides and preservatives with a desire, passion and wherewithal to penetrate 
markets on a global scale," states Michael DelliCompagni, Chief Operating Officer 
of Special Materials Company. "SMC brings its market, customer, distribution and 
manufacturing expertise making DBSM Biocides the new flexible alternative to the 
current market supply status quo."
Xianwu Liu Chairman of Dalian Bio-Chem comments, "In today's global economy, 
I and my US partner SMC would like to help our customers to succeed in what they 
are doing. With our combined capabilities, we are in a good position to satisfy 
the current needs of the U.S. market."

June 4, 2014 - New York, NY - Charlie Neale Appointed New Oil & Gas Manager with Special Materials Company 
We are pleased to announce Charlie Neale has joined Special Materials Company 
as its new Oil & Gas Manager in the North American region. 
Mr. Neale will be responsible for the management and support of key accounts 
and the sales strategy of SMC Oil & Gas Business and will be based in Louisiana.

Charlie Neale is a qualified microbiologist and water treatment expert. He 
holds a Bachelor of Science in Microbiology from Southeastern Louisiana State 
University as well as graduate studies in Aquatic Toxicology and Environmental 
Management. 
He has over 24 years' experience in specialty chemicals predominantly in 
industrial water treatment applications, waste remediation and most recently Oil 
& Gas applications. 
Charlie Neale has worked for Callaway Chemicals / Vulcan Performance 
Chemicals in the 1990's and more recently with Kemira as Key Account Manager Oil 
& Gas in Holden, Louisiana. 
"We are delighted that Charlie has joined the SMC team to strengthen our 
technical and sales expertise in both our Oil & Gas and Water Treatment business 
verticals; with an emphasis on biocides and new business development. As we 
build our organization we look for the best and the brightest and clearly 
Charlie exemplifies these traits. His reputation in the market speaks for 
itself," said Michael DelliCompagni, Special Materials Company Chief Operating 
Office (COO).

December 5, 2013 - New York, NY - Jeffrey M. Watson Appointed New Product Manager for Special Materials Company
Special Materials Company (SMC) has appointed Jeffrey M. Watson as a new company Product Manager. With over 13 years of experience in the chemical industry, he brings not only a wealth of knowledge to the position but he rounds out Special Materials Company (SMC) already strong and entrepreneurial product team.

According to Adam Feldman, Special Materials Company CEO "Our goal is to use all of our strengths, creativity, and energy to help and support not only our customers, partners and suppliers to reach the goals and objectives, but our employees, too. We know that our continuing success is built on every interaction that we have with all of them. Our reputation grows by doing this diligently and carefully. And I am sure that Jeff Watson's contribution to the company will be very valuable.

Jeff Watson summarized why he joined Special Materials Company (SMC) by stating, "I am extremely excited to join Special Materials Company and appreciate the opportunity to be part of such an enthusiastic organization. SMC has demonstrated significant growth for many years.  I strive to support SMC and the goal of further growth.  The energy and entrepreneurial spirit is encouraging and I hope to bring my knowledge and skills to contribute to further success".

Prior to joining Special Materials Company (SMC), Jeff held key development and account managing positions at Cognis Corp., Arkema Inc., and Rhodia/Solvay.
October 10th, 2013 - Expansion of Aryl Phosphines and Phosphinic Acids Production Capacity
SMC has completed its latest capacity expansion of aryl phosphines and phosphinic acids at its Yancheng, Jiangsu, China, joint venture plant. The facility will increase production of Benzene Phosphinic Acid (BZPA, a.k.a. Phenylphosphonic acid) as well as production of the phosphinate salts Sodium Benzene Phosphinate (Na-BZPA) and Potassium Benzene Phosphinate (K-BZPA).

"Our Yancheng facility is an excellent base of operations to address the current market's needs.  Aryl phosphorous derivatives find use as building blocks for a variety of niche industrial applications such as catalysts and intermediates in the fields of high performance polymers, yarn production, metal recovery, corrosion protection in metalworking fluids, dispersants, and lubricity of high-temperature greases," said Kevin Huber, Executive Vice President of Special Materials Company.

In addition to the new Aryl Phosphines expansion; the Yancheng site produces Phosphorous based flame retardants.
September 26th, 2013 - Avancid®75 biocide Earns U.S. Environmental Protection Agency Registration for use in Industrial Water Treatment and Oilfield Applications
Special Materials Company (SMC) is pleased to announce that the US Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) has granted registration to the company's Avancid®75 biocide product for use in water treatment and oilfield applications.  Avancid®75 biocide is a seventy five percent solution of tetrakis (hydroxymethyl) phosphonium sulfate (THPS), a widely used and highly effective chemistry for water treatment. 

According to Tom Haack, Global Business Manager at Special Materials Company, "Avancid®75 biocide provides our customers with a more cost-effective solution for mitigating problems associated with bacterial growth in industrial and oilfield water systems than has previously been available to them. Our company philosophy has always been to offer superior products with proven performances at a very competitive price and Avancid®75 biocide delivers all that."

Avancid®75 biocide is a fast-acting microbiocide that controls troublesome bacteria and dissolves iron sulfide at low use levels.  It is stable and effective in high sulfide environments, and is recognized for its benign environmental profile and rapid decomposition after discharge.  These properties make it a product of choice for oil recovery operations and industrial water treatment systems.
Avancid®75 biocide is a registered trademark of Special Materials Company.
September 9th, 2013 - Michael DelliCompagni appointed new Chief Operating Officer.
Specialty Materials Company (SMC) is pleased to announce the appointment of Mr. Michael DelliCompagni as its new Chief Operating Officer ("COO").  Mr. DelliCompagni, who joins Special Materials Company after more than 22 years with Brenntag North America, has commenced with SMC in early September 2013.   Mr. DelliCompagni was formerly the Director of Sales and Sourcing for Brenntag North America. In this role he led Brenntag's North American Sales and Sourcing team, comprised of presidents, vice presidents and company executives in developing supply and sales strategies for key product lines. 
 
Commenting on the appointment of Mr. DelliCompagni, Adam Feldman, SMC's Chief Executive Officer said: "A proven and effective leader, Michael possesses a diverse and extensive background including Sales, Business Development, Operations, Marketing, e-Business, New Business Start-Up, Sourcing, Strategic Relations and Contract Negotiations.  As we continue to grow, we need to focus on providing strategic direction and operational support to SMC's successful and growing specialty chemical business and establish more of a leadership and management structure to help us to do what we need to do in an efficient, productive manner."  Adam Feldman continues by saying, "I am confident that in his new position as Chief Operating Officer, Michael will continue to successfully identify opportunities from new and existing markets to further develop our specialty chemical niche products and services to allow Special Materials Company to remain at the forefront of our industry."
 
Mr. DelliCompagni, Chief Operating Officer of SMC comments, "I am extremely excited and fortunate to join Special Materials Company.  SMC has grown to be the 28th largest chemical distributor in the United States and in the top 100 chemical distributors globally.  In addition to chemical distribution, SMC is also a very successful chemical producer.  Their entrepreneurial spirit has been at the core of their success.  This is substantiated by the fact that Adam Feldman, CEO of Special Materials Company, has recently been recognized by Ernst and Young, NY as the 2013 Entrepreneur of the year.  As SMC's tag line states 'Providing a Competitive Advantage', there is passion throughout the organization to be unique and to satisfy the customers' needs in any way possible.  SMC's approach to the market is quite distinctive and the caliber of people are best in class.   As I strive to provide leadership and structure, I will not lose sight of the entrepreneurial spirit that has made SMC the company it is today.  As Chief Operating Officer, I look forward to sharing my knowledge and experience across the company and supporting SMC in its goal for further growth and success in the specialty chemical industry."
July 19th, 2013 - Special Materials Co. (SMC) Makes the ICIS Top 100 Chemical Distributors List 2013.
Special Materials Co. ("SMC") has made the ICIS Top 100 Chemical Distributors list this year. SMC stands proudly No. 71 of the Top 100 and No.28 in the North America region. ICIS Chemical Business magazine ranked the companies by 2012 sales, reporting that Special Materials Co. had sales of $171 million that year.
 
"We are thrilled to be ranked in the Top 100 Chemical Distributors and it's very gratifying to see our name listed among all these chemical industry leaders. The credit goes to our expanding customer base and our dedicated employees worldwide," said CEO, Adam Feldman. "We are developing leading positions in many niche industrial products since our size and structure gives us the flexibility to grow and adapt to market needs much more quickly than other companies."
 
Coupled with its local presence, Special Materials Co. is utilizing its offices in Europe, Latin America, and China to generate new opportunities and provide stronger support to both national and international key accounts. Also, it is expanding services such as warehousing, mixing, blending, and dispersing activities in its 40,000 sq. ft. facility located in Kershaw, South Carolina. "Kershaw's Toll-manufacturing Solutions can provide companies with the opportunity to decrease costs and increase profits. Our employees are focused, and 100% committed to do our best" said Kevin Huber, Executive Vice President of Special Materials Co.
June 18th, 2013 - Chief Executive Adam Feldman Named Ernst & Young Entrepreneur Of The Year® 2013 Award Winner in New York.
Co-Founder and CEO, Adam Feldman received the Ernst & Young Entrepreneur Of The Year® 2013 Award in New York. This award recognizes outstanding high-growth entrepreneurs who demonstrate excellence and extraordinary success in such areas as innovation, financial performance and personal commitment to their businesses and communities.

 
The award recipients were selected by an independent judging panel made up of regional business, academic and community leaders and previous Entrepreneur Of The Year award recipients.
"This award is an acknowledgment of the success of SMC.  I want to thank Mark Silver and Kevin Huber, my partners, and the rest of the SMC family of employees and advisors who are responsible for our success.  This award is outside confirmation of what we all know; that we are a unique special company" said CEO Adam Feldman.
 
As a New York award winner, Mr. Feldman is now eligible for consideration for the Ernst & Young LLP Entrepreneur of The Year 2013 national program.  Award winners in several national categories, as well as the National Entrepreneur of The Year Overall Award winner, will be announced at the annual awards gala in Palm Springs, California, on November 16, 2013. The awards are the culminating event of the Ernst & Young Strategic Growth Forum®, the nation's most prestigious gathering of high-growth, market-leading companies.
 
Now in its 27th year, the Entrepreneur Of The Year Program has honored the inspirational leadership of such entrepreneurs as Howard Schultz of Starbucks Coffee Company, Arthur M. Blank of AMB Group, LLC (The Home Depot, Atlanta Falcons), Pierre Omidyar of eBay Inc., Ruth Fertel of Ruth's Chris Steak House, Maxine Clark of Build-A-Bear Workshop, Inc., Tom Adams of Rosetta Stone, Reid Hoffman and Jeff Weiner of LinkedIn, and 2012 winner Hamdi Ulukaya, founder of Chobani Inc.
June 17th, 2013 - Perry Collins appointed new Regulatory Affairs Manager.
SMC announces the appointment of Perry Collins as its new Regulatory Affairs Manager in light of the retirement of Mr. Phil Ostrowski after five years of impeccable service.
 
In his new position, Mr. Collins will be responsible for ensuring SMC is compliant to applicable industry and government standards, both domestically and globally and will be based at SMC's Production and Warehousing Facility in Kershaw, South Carolina. In addition, Mr. Collins brings 36 years of professional experience within the chemical industry and prior to his position at SMC, he served as Manager of Environmental Health and Safety at WeylChem US Inc.
 
"SMC is always looking for seasoned professionals to defy the odds and overcome the challenges of the highly complex and ever-changing environment of our industry. We are pleased to welcome Perry and will lean on his professional experience and solid background to help further SMC's footprint" said Kevin Huber, Executive Vice President at Special Materials Company.
 
Perry Collins is an active member of SOCMA's ChemStewards® program and has participated as an Environmental, Health, Safety & Security (EHSS) auditor.
