December 12th, 2011 - SMC To Increase Sodium Cyanida Prices ...
                        
                        Special Materials Company announced today that effective January 1st, 2012 it will increase the price of its sodium cyanide grades to all its customers by $0.20/LB ($0.44/KG). The increase is necessary due to current market conditions driven by the impressive rise of gold prices.
    According to SMC officials, "We have always worked very hard to offer our customers products at affordable prices and have already implemented a strategy to diminish the price increase."
                        
December 2nd, 2011 - SMC Relocates Cyanide's Inventory ...
                        
                       As supply chain costs continue to rise and the supply chain grows more and more complex, Special Materials Company is looking for best practices for improving its inventory management strategy. SMC is relocating its inventory of sodium cyanide from a public warehouse to its owned facility in Kershaw, SC to minimize the challenges of fulfilling customer demand. "Storing cyanide products at the Kershaw, SC facility will reduce handling and packaging costs. In addition, SMC will gain complete control of the security and supply chain management of this hazardous product" said product manager Michael Norwood.
                        
October 15th, 2011 - SPECIAL MATERIALS COMPANY TO RAISE THE PRICE ...

                        
                       New York, NY?Special Materials Company (SMC) is increasing effective immediately or as contracts allow, pricing for PCBTF (parachlorobenzotrifluoride) by 10% covering all grades and packages.
    
    This action is necessary to respond to raw material market conditions and currency exchange challenges. Environmental issues have caused production challenges for key raw materials along with unexpected strong demand for PCBTF for the agricultural market.
    
    According to SMC's Compliance Solutions Product Manager, Diane Tramontana, "SMC remains committed to supplying high quality PCBTF and maintaining sufficient US based inventory to supply the market demand"
                        
