May 23rd, 2011 - Partnership with Gustavo Russo ...

                        
                       Special Materials Company (SMC) is pleased to announce that it has entered into a partnership with Gustavo Russo to build a Latin American Specialty Chemical business.
    
    SMC, formed in 1996, with headquarters in New York City, is a global specialty chemical company serving global markets in agriculture, energy, paint and coatings, paper, cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, and intermediates. SMC has been growing its business at a 25% per year compounded rate. Currently at USD120 Million in sales, it is the right size to provide a level of dedication and service to its customers which is unequaled in its market segments. SMC has ownership of 3 factories in China, and one factory in the United States with several logistics distribution centers across the globe.
    
    With this association with Gustavo Russo, SMC is building a platform in Latin America to market products, provide logistics services, and invest through acquisitions and Joint Ventures. The office, located in Campinas City Estate of Sao Paulo in a privileged geographic area of Brazil, will supervise SMC's activities in Latin America and will have a local logistics team providing an improved level of service in the Latin America region.
    
    SMC and Russo are committed to making Latin America a more significant part of its global business, and supporting the growing economies in Brazil and Latin America.
    
    Adam Feldman
    Chief Executive Officer
    Special Materials Company
                        
April 15th, 2011 - Implementing an approximately 15% price increase ...

New York, NY----- Special Materials Company (SMC) is implementing an approximately 15% price increase effective immediately or as contracts allow. SMC also instituted order control for PCBTF as of April 1, 2011.
    
    These actions are necessary to respond to abrupt and significant increases in certain raw material costs, and continuing upward pressure from energy, currency and freight costs. According to Diane Tramontana, SMC's Compliance Solution's Product Manager, "This situation may to continue into the third quarter of 2011. We are sparing no effort to keep customers well supplied during this difficult period, and can see the market coming into balance later in the year, but until then, we need to manage our supply carefully."
About Special Materials Company
    SMC is a global marketer, manufacturer and developer of specialty chemical products. The company main activities are in the manufacture of phosphorous derivatives, alkyl phosphines, photographic and motion picture chemicals, and specialty flame retardants. In addition, the company distributes solvents, resin additives and titanium dioxide slurry through a global net of warehouses.
                        
